  "prompt": "Why is Manaphy annoying in Pokemon ranger and the temple of the sea?",
  "response": "In \"Pok\u00e9mon Ranger: Guardian Signs\" and \"Pok\u00e9mon: The Temple of the Sea,\" Manaphy can be considered annoying for a few reasons:\n\n1. **Time Limit in Ranger**: In \"Pok\u00e9mon Ranger,\" capturing Manaphy requires the player to connect with it multiple times, which can be challenging given the time constraints of the Capture Styler. If players are not quick or strategic enough, they may fail and have to restart the capture attempt.\n\n2. **Movement Pattern**: Manaphy has a unique movement pattern, which can make it difficult to capture. Its ability to move quickly can frustrate players, especially if they're not adept at using the Capture Styler.\n\n3. **Mission Complexity**: In \"Z\" \"Temple of the Sea,\" the subplot involving Manaphy revolves around protecting it and ensuring it reaches its destination, which can involve navigating through challenges and battling enemies. This can add layers of complexity that some players might find tedious.\n\n4. **Emotional Attachment**: Manaphy is portrayed as an important and beloved character in the movie. Players might feel a sense of urgency or frustration while trying to protect and support it, amplifying any annoyance encountered during gameplay.\n\nOverall, the combination of its capture mechanics and the narrative surrounding it contributes to why players might find Manaphy annoying in these contexts.",
